The total voting count may also be made if at the end of the ordinary computer it is established that the difference between the allegedly winning candidate and the second-place candidate is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is an express request from the political party's representative whose candidate remained second, in which case the electoral packages that have been partially accounted for will be excluded.
